A terminally-ill grandmother met her best friend for the last time after she was flown to the UK from Australia thanks to donations from generous strangers. Janet Clark was told in November that her pancreatic cancer was incurable and she would need end-of-life care. She told her family she was desperate to see her closest pal Vanessa Evans before she died. Janet met Vanessa when she lived in Australia and developed a sister-like bond with her over the decade they knew each other down under.Â Derbyshire Live reports. But Janet, of Alvaston, Derby, left the country for the UK again in 2003 when her husband passed away.    